RACE.RACE_TEXT: SANTA ANITA PARK RACE 1 5 1/2F Turf CR: 101. Starter Allowance Purse 40000. FOR THREE YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE STARTED FOR A CLAIMING PRICE OF $50,000 OR LESS AND WHICH HAVE NEVER WON THREE RACES. Three Year Olds, 118 lbs.; Older, 126 lbs. (Rail at 30 feet).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: CHERUBIC FACTOR unhurried in the beginning, raced outside a rival at the back into the turn, gained around the bend while easing out and loomed three wide into the stretch, took over with a furlong remaining and maintained a short lead over DONCIC to the wire. DONCIC raced up close three deep early, bid two wide with a quarter mile left to run, took over entering the stretch, lost command a furlong out but stayed on gamely to the wire. INCH sat off the pace, got blocked entering the first turn, moved out around the bend and three to four wide into the stretch, moved out a bit further in the lane and gained the show. LAW ABIDING brushed leaving the gate, went up to set the pace inside a pair of rivals, cleared briefly on the turn before being challenged by DONCIC, lost the lead nearing the stretch and gave way. SHUT UP MICHAEL (IRE) chased between then angled down to the inside, hugged the rail through the bend, tipped out in the stretch and lacked a rally. STORMY SAMURAI brushed with LAW ABIDING at the start, pressed the pace between rivals, chased the leader two wide around the turn and weakened. HAND-TIMED.

RACE.FOOTNOTES: IN COLOR was tossing her head around in the gate then hopped and stumbled when the gates opened, stalked the top trio from outside leaving the backstretch, launched a bid four deep and took over at the quarter pole, cleared three wide into the stretch and drew off under right then left hand urging. IRRESISTIBLE FORCE dueled for command outside a rival early, led briefly between rivals at the five-sixteenths pole but relinquished the lead shortly after, chased along the rail into the drive and churned on to regain the place from TENNESSEE MOON in the furlong grounds. TENNESSEE MOON bobbled leaving the gate, pressed the pace outside a dueling pair, vied three deep around the bend between rivals, chased the winner two wide into the drive and flattened to third. OUR KENTUCKY ROSE was fractious in the starting gate and had to be backed out and reloaded, broke slow and dropped back early, trailed on the inside then tipped out into the stretch and failed to menace. PAID IN GOLD fractious in the gate, dueled inside IRRESISTIBLE FORCE early, held a short lead over outside rivals to the five-sixteenths pole, lost command and stayed on to the quarter pole, then started to lose ground into the stretch and gave way.

RACE.FOOTNOTES: MOTOWN MUSIC forwardly placed from inside early, moved out and chased two wide on the far turn, drew alongside ROYAL ACT midstretch, got floated out and brushed by that rival while dueling and edged by late. ROYAL ACT was off a bit slow to begin, stalked four wide around the clubhouse turn, drew alongside the top pair up the backstretch, took over at the three-eighths pole then cleared BOLD ENDEAVOR and steered inside late on the far turn, challenged by MOTOWN MUSIC past the eighth pole, drifted out under left-handed urging to brush that rival, fought through deep stretch and yielded grudgingly. ZIMBA WARRIOR unhurried in the beginning and moved inside, went around weakening rival and moved out to three path on the far turn, kept on through the lane and was along for the show. BOLD ENDEAVOR raced up close outside the leader early, challenged for command up the backstretch, took over at the seven-sixteenths pole, was overtaken by ROYAL act at the three-eighths pole, moved to the rail on the far turn, chased into the lane and weakened. BALADI was off slow in the beginning, reserved two to three wide early outside a rival, tugged into and early on the backstretch, chased three deep then two wide on the far turn and weakened. IMPOSSIBLE TASK led in the two path into the first turn then moved inside, dueled with BOLD ENDEAVOR up the backstretch, dropped back on the far turn and faded.
